acred role of proscenium arches, the necessity of live audiences, and the ritualistic purity of stagecraft.\n\nWithout realizing it, Henry found himself engaged in conversation with $entity_1, the woman in the blue gown. His fingers, once tangled in uncertainty, now traced ideas in the air like a magician’s wand. “You talk so much about the old ways,” she observed quietly"